fields.quote: Life is not measured by the number of breaths we take, but by the moments that take our breath away.
You take your life in your own hands, and what happens? A terrible thing, no one to blame.
It is not what you do for your children, but what you have taught them to do for themselves, that will make them successful human beings.
What’s money? A man is a success if he gets up in the morning and goes to bed at night and in between does what he wants to do.
Whatever the mind of man can conceive and believe, it can achieve.
Everything has beauty, but not everyone can see.
We can easily forgive a child who is afrapk of the dark; the real tragedy of life is when men are afrapk of the light.
Remember no one can make you feel inferior without your consent.
Too many of us are not living our dreams because we are living our fears.
Eighty percent of success is showing up.
